data.title: Medal of Honor Recipient
data.meta_description: U.S. Army Private  James W Webb was presented the Medal of Honor for military valor during the U.S. Civil War.
data.text:
U.S. Civil War - U.S. Army

James W Webb

Details

Rank: Private (Highest Rank: Brevet Captain)

Conflict/Era: U.S. Civil War

Unit/Command:

Company F,

5th New York Infantry

Military Service Branch: U.S. Army

Medal of Honor Action Date: August 30, 1862

Medal of Honor Action Place: Bull Run, Virginia, USA

Citation

Under heavy fire voluntarily carried information to a battery commander that enabled him to save his guns from capture. Was severely wounded, but refused to go to the hospital and participated in the remainder of the campaign.
